---
---
<section class="py-16 bg-brand-softBg border-b border-brand-border/30">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          What can TheEduAssist build in Kajabi?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          TheEduAssist can support course structure, Course setup, website and landing pages, Products, Offers, checkout, email journeys, Automations, migration, testing and ongoing improvement. The exact scope depends on the client’s goals and Kajabi plan.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Can you improve an existing Kajabi website?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. Existing pages, navigation, mobile layouts, branding, lead journeys and customer access can be reviewed and improved. Legacy templates may require a controlled rebuild rather than an automatic transfer.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Can you migrate an existing course to Kajabi?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. TheEduAssist can audit the source material, map the curriculum, prepare content, rebuild the course and test access. Available migration options depend on the source platform and its export capabilities.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Do you help organize course content?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. Course architecture and instructional design are central parts of the service. Existing books, videos, documents and training materials can be organized into modules, lessons, activities and learner resources.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Can you configure Products, Offers and checkout?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. Support can include Product setup, Offer configuration, pricing, checkout design, customer access, coupons and post-purchase destinations. Feature availability can depend on the Kajabi account and payment setup.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Can you create email campaigns and Automations?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. TheEduAssist can map and configure lead, purchase, onboarding and learner communication flows using the tools available in the client’s Kajabi plan.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Can you improve the customer Library experience?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. Support can include Library organization, Product naming, thumbnails, navigation, login guidance and testing of the customer-access journey.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          Do you provide ongoing Kajabi support?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          Yes. Ongoing support may include page updates, Course changes, new Offers, email adjustments, Automation testing, QA and launch support.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white border border-brand-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-1.5 p-4 text-brand-navy font-bold">
          What happens during the Kajabi Review?
          <svg class="size-5 shrink-0 transition duration-300 group-open:-rotate-180" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-4 border-t border-brand-border/50 text-brand-textMain">
          TheEduAssist reviews the submitted information about the client’s current or planned Kajabi setup and recommends the clearest next step. It is not a promise that the complete project will be delivered within 24–48 hours.
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
